# Git branch naming

Working branches must follow **`<type>/<short-description>`**. The pre-push hook
([`.husky/pre-push`](../../.husky/pre-push)) rejects any branch outside this policy.

## Allowed names

| Kind | Pattern | Examples |
| ---- | ------- | -------- |
| Long-lived (environments) | `dev`, `main` | `dev`, `main` |
| Working branch | `<type>/<short-description>` | `feature/ai-stream-response`, `fix/login-error` |
| AI web session | `claude/<slug>` | `claude/vigilant-hopper-cbl23b` |

**Allowed `<type>` values:** `feat`, `feature`, `fix`, `hotfix`, `refactor`,
`docs`, `test`, `chore`, `ci`, `perf`, `build`, `style`, `revert`
(`feat` and `feature` are both accepted; conventional-commit types are mirrored).
Canonical human reference: [`docs/process/git-workflow.md`](../../docs/process/git-workflow.md).

## `claude/*` is platform-assigned, not chosen here

Claude Code **web/cloud** sessions do **not** reliably pick their branch name from
inside the repo. The platform creates the task branch and clones the repo onto it
**before** the container and the agent start, and the cloud git proxy may restrict
pushes to that working branch. Repo skills, rules, and hooks run *inside* the
session and cannot rename it — so `claude/*` is allowlisted by design. To land web
work under a `feature/`/`fix/` name, rename at the PR/merge layer or teleport the
session to a local checkout; do not fight the proxy from inside the session.

## When creating a branch yourself

- Branch from `dev` (hotfixes from `main`): `git checkout dev && git pull && git checkout -b feature/<slug>`.
- In a Claude Code web session you are bound to the assigned `claude/*` branch
  and must not switch branches without explicit user permission.
- Bypass the hook for a one-off push with `SKIP_BRANCH_CHECK=1 git push` (prefer
  renaming the branch instead).
